message: New research shows that underage victims are increasingly likely to first meet their trafficker online, and the majority of underage victims have been advertised or sold online. How is it that America’s children can be sold online like a t-shirt or take-out?

data.description: Section 230 of the Communications Decency Act of 1996 has been interpreted so broadly that courts have ruled in favor of websites like Backpage.com, despite clear criminal conduct.
data.title: Congresswoman Ann Wagner - Congress Never Intended to Enable Sex Trafficking Crime Online-This Bill Will Change That
